      "message": "One more: I try to avoid parenthetical comments because:\n- as a reader, I don\u0027t know what they are trying to tell me (i.e., is this information assumed? optional? unnecessary?) \n- I parse parentheses sometimes to mean math, (1 + 2) * 3.\n\n- I also try to avoid abbreviations for the non-English native speaker because they add another level of indirection, e.g., adds Latin to our working vocabulary.\n\nI would probably word this as:\n\n\"Text encoding describes how to interpret the text bytes pass to methods like measureText() and drawText().\"",
